"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-09-paris-2024-olympics-nigeria-disqualified-from-mens-4x400m-relay-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Nigerian men's 4x400m team has been disqualified from competing in the final of the event.  The quartet of Emmanuel Ojeli, Ezekiel Nathanial, Dubem Amene and Chidi Okezie sealed a place in the final after finishing second in heat 1 behind France.  They ran a season's best time of 2:59.81.  The Nigerians were, disqualified for stepping on the line in their heat.  Belgium has now moved to second position, with South Africa stepping up to third position.  The quartet's hopes of emulating the 2000 and 2004 teams that won gold and bronze in Sydney and Athens have now been dashed.  Paris 2024 Olympics: Amusan crashes out in women's 100m hurdles  True warrior - Ramos reacts to Pepe's retirement  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"